author: 13abc
title: Victim identified in fatal crash in Fostoria
text:
Camden man dead (Courtesy: MGN Online)
FOSTORIA, Ohio (13abc Action News) - Ohio Highway Patrol confirmed the identity of 48-year-old Gary B. Hernandez of Toledo, who died in a single-vehicle crash in Fostoria Thursday.
The crash happened around 1:42 Thursday afternoon on SR 199, just south of Stearns Rd.
Hernandez was driving a 2007 Chevrolet Utilimaster Van.
The van traveled off the right side of the road, struck a street sign and a utility pole, and rolled over.
Hernandez was not wearing his safety belt, and was ejected from the van. He was pronounced deceased at the scene.
Investigators don't suspect alcohol or drugs to be factors.
